{
  "stem": "11642.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And my father used to say, you come on in because your rabbi is in here waiting for you.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And when I saw that rabbi, I didn't like him to come and take me away.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But my father said-- and this, I always remember the rest of my life-- anything what you possess, you might lose in your life, but not what will sticks to your brains.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Until today, I know so.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sometimes I'm with a group of people where they asking, who knows how to read Hebrew and who knows how to read Jewish?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I can raise my hand, because I know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this is thanks because my parents put a lot of effort in education.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Did you have any siblings?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Living in Poland?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I did.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Going to school, a lots of time-- especially when came before the holidays, Christmas-- we felt it, that we are Jewish, because we were afraid to go out in the street.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And also remember, very well, being told, when I got in a sort of dispute or something with a girlfriend at school, that she used to say, why-- if you don't like it here, why don't you go back to your own country?",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But you can't, because you don't have it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's why today, with me-- I can pick up my head high enough.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And proud that I am able-- and thankful to God-- to contribute today to work what I'm doing to keep up our country.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And our children, grandchildren, and forever generations to come should have a country.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Israel should be alive.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had two brothers and one sister.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my sister's name was Sarah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My brother's name was David.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the youngest one, who was only six when the war broke out, he-- his name was Hersch.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
